<Folder><name>Scenic Points</name><Placemark><name>Chéticamp</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Acadian fishing village — French-speaking, hooked-rug heritage, Le Gabriel restaurant. Whale-watching tours from the harbor.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-61.015200,46.624300,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Skyline Trail</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[7 km loop hike to a headland boardwalk overlooking the Cabot Trail switchbacks below. Best at sunset; moose feed in the meadows.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-60.955000,46.740000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Pleasant Bay</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Pilot whale interpretive center; tours run mid-July to August. Whale Interpretive Centre has a real pilot-whale skeleton.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-60.799000,46.826500,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Lone Shieling</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Replica of a Scottish stone shepherd's hut, set in a 350-year-old sugar maple grove. Short walk from parking.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-60.697500,46.834700,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Cape Smokey</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[365 m headland over the Atlantic — gondola-accessible, often misted in. Eagles and gannets in summer.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-60.353000,46.628000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Alexander Graham Bell Museum</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[In Baddeck — Bell summered here for 35 years. Original hydrofoil HD-4 (1919 world speed record holder) on display.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-60.757200,46.087600,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark></Folder>
